text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia nivea is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The bushy rounded shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 3 metres (5 to 10 ft). It blooms from August to October and produces yellow flowers.
